7:
No matter where you go, everyone's
up in arms. It's like we've gone thirty
years back in time.
9:
What do you want to do? If we're not
careful, cutting out the pus might
leave us open to infection.
13:
We can't stop what we've already
set in motion. However, what we can
change is our approach.
22:
*sigh* As if I could ever say no to
that...
25: That was one heck of a sigh.
29:
Well, that's what happens when
you're tired. I might need to cash in
that favor you owe me soon.
41:
It may not be our home, but
Palpebra holds a special place in
our hearts.
49:
Ah, to be young again... Wait, Stella's
a lot older than us, right?
59:
We think so. Someone on the inside
must be helping smuggle cryptic
artifacts out of the Kaleidoscope.
62:
Not exactly a pleasant thought, is it?
It gets even worse when you realize
they've been doing this for a LONG
time.
71:
No way. Cryptic artifacts aren't
worth enough to warrant the risk.
However...
75:
It WOULD make sense if someone is
blackmailing the smugglers—and
Palpebra—into complying.
78:
Not sure what dirt the blackmailer
has, but my guess is it has
something to do with the incident 30
years ago.
81:
Are you talking about the
assassination of the Farlands
princess?
85:
Yeah, things got pretty ugly for a
while there. Neither side wanted to
take the blame.
88:
If Palpebra is hiding something
about the incident, well... Smuggling
a suspect out of Palpebra is a small
price to pay for someone's silence.
96:
I know. The Farlands were behind
her death.
99:
Let's just say I had the chance to
speak with an eyewitness. The
Kweturs are behind her death,
correct?
101:
That means another assassination
could happen at any time. The
whole thing's a bomb ready to go
off.
105:
So they're being blackmailed into
complying.
111:
Both sides are hiding secrets that
could blow the lives of their citizens
sky-high.
114:
And I'm starting to think the same
person is holding both detonators.
117:
Fearful of the truth, we instead
continue the comfortable lie. Hard
to believe we're so weak, huh?
121:
No, I... think I've come to understand
their perspective now...
130:
...Anyway, what do you want us to
do, Zekhel?
134:
As my wonderful subordinates have
discovered, our enemy holds the
fate of our world in their hands.
137:
So... I'd like to make use of your
connections.
147: I see what you mean now...
151:
Wahaha! Interesting! Well, Procheon
DOES owe me a favor. I think it's
about time I collect on it!
156:
Haha... Careful, you're already on the
suspect list for working with him.
161:
Oh dear, it seems my reputation
precedes me!
165:
The Star Augurs... I will admit that
their presence does concern me.
170:
Are you perhaps referring to the
oracle's creation?
174:
Yes. While I was regrettably unaware
of their actions at the time, I have
read the reports...
176:
Many people were a part of the
Resistance. Even those outside
Stratos.
181:
Perhaps even... drifters from other
worlds?
186:
Indeed. The origins of some of the
participants are shrouded in
mystery... I intend to investigate this
myself.
190:
I'll lend a hand too. Apparently my
absence gave some groups an
excuse to cause trouble.
192:
I'm sure the Crimson Blades can
handle it. If not, I know a certain
mermaid will be more than willing to
lend me a fin.
197: Thank you all. I owe you one.
202:
By the way... Are you a smoker,
Zekhel?
205:
You've been fidgeting with your
pocket for a while now. The tell-tale
sign of a smoker.
209:
Ah, well... Not anymore. A special
someone made it very clear she
doesn't like the smell.
213:
Aww, too bad. I thought maybe we
could share a quick smoke break.
218:
Heh, don't be such a worrywart. I'm
not planning to steal your precious
Marina away.
221:
Besides, she's waaay too young for
me.
228:
SHE'S too young for you? What
about Kugala?
232:
Uh... Kugala's a lot older than Marina
here. And I'm not interested in her
either.
240:
Come on, Alk. You should know
better than to judge a sheephird's
age from their appearance.
244:
Alk... What are you so surprised for?
Surely I don't look THAT old to you...
249: U-um... I, uh, I didn't mean—
261:
Here's your share, Captain! I saved it
just for you.
265:
Don't even think about running
away. You're staying the night, and
that's that!
269:
It'd be nice to hear that in a more
ROMANTIC setting, but oh well...
272:
I suppose I should do my job every
now and the—
277:
Hey there, girlie. Long time no see.
You here to reward me?
280:
See? I don't smell like cigarettes
anymore, do I?
286:
Haha. Looks like quitting smoking
was worth it after all.
290:
All right... Care to join me for some
overtime?
